{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0760cac0-b2bf-4e07-8e6b-c214d13d2c88","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed **before** them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_ZCRZp2BNSoW38N3ppDsYd8","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-ae4867dbac6f4eeb8bf41c9e0b63a0bf/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-ae4867dbac6f4eeb8bf41c9e0b63a0bf/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"4c9d396e-1ca2-4e38-9f15-389d12be140a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` has `open BrokenOrder.Domain`, meaning it depends on `Domain.fs`. Since `Domain.fs` comes after `Services.fs` in the compile order, this will fail.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs` (defines the types)\n\n\n2. `Services.fs` (uses the types from Domain)\n3. `Program.fs` (uses both Domain and Services)","outputTokens":469,"requestId":"F034:203FDB:456B6E5:4D12005:69F9B07D"},"id":"3323deb1-4e55-47a3-83a6-1112182d319e","timestamp":"2026-05-05T08:55:32.909Z","parentId":"4d7fa847-0b92-451a-befd-ab7ec527da02"}
